sence mij last of 17 cur, non from you so refeme you to the
same, this this easterley windes keep our ships att your side
so you have time to compleate my orders, there is a convoy arrived

remitt you £104:½ on John hillcosdon samuel Blewitt procure

on the 10 cur was to you my last sence non from you, inclosd

on david becceler & comp please to procure the needfull & when
in cas returne the vallew in bills att 2 a 3 usance, as you shall
iudge to my advantage, cost mee 28: t these cost 28: 2 en &
remitt not withont I can have an intrest, for by a fallinge exe
I shall imploye in londen & what you s hall doe for mee I shall
allow ¼ CPc for standing del credere so as you have proyssed, whee

Londer samuel beewith
sence my last of 3 cur non from you inclosed a perfect invoyce of your
pack of tijkes, which was the 10 cur att bridges, & sent the next
morninge att ostend, & come butt 4 houres to lase the convoij beeng
sailed the same morning & though I have been att some extraordinarie
charges from gand to ostend, yett itt hath been inipossible to have the
pack sooner att ostend, now I know not if itt bee not your advantage
that the pack come to late, because severall of the merchand men are
come back att ostend by contrarie wind though the convoy held gea
with the rest whereof wee have no news, so you must have patience
bill the first opportunitie, which wee hoye vere soon, because most o
the merchandmen are still att ostend, I exspect the bill of loadinge
as soon as shipped, which shall send you, the cost is ƒ 881:16:

£104:19:6 payable to mre walt & will kent which
